                <head>165. Editorial Note</head>
                <p>Between January 20 and 23, President <persName corresp="#p_FA1">Arturo
                        Frondizi</persName>, accompanied by senior Argentine officials, paid a State
                    visit to the United States. President <persName corresp="#p_FA1"
                        >Frondizi</persName> had conversations with President
                        <persName>Eisenhower</persName>, Secretary <persName corresp="#p_DJF1"
                        >Dulles</persName>, and other administration officials. During his visit,
                        <persName corresp="#p_FA1">Frondizi</persName> addressed a joint meeting of
                    Congress. For text of the address, see Department of State <hi rend="italic"
                        >Bulletin</hi>, February 23, 1959, pages 280–283.</p>
            </div>
